text: <@U4V5EHQ2G> I think it comes down to whether you plan on casting several artifacts a turn via loops where key becomes better.
check the mana curve of those 36. cloud key is better when you want to cast more than one thing in a turn, and if curve is too high that won't happen anyway
e.g. if all your artifacts are 1-drops, then cloud key empties your hand
if your artifacts are 7-drops, then maybe you cast one of them 1 turn early
so low curve = better cloud key
similar to [[edgewalker]]... i don't run that when my commander is a 5-cmc cleric. i do run it when i have 30 [[shadowborn apostles]]

text: so maybe add up the cmc of the artifacts, subtract 1 for each artifact, and the remainder would indicate how good cloud key would be with the rest of the deck (lower remainder = better)
better fitness function... add up (1 / cmc of each artifact) to represent the % savings, higher number is better.
edgewalker would have a score of 30 * (1 / 1) in a 30-shadowborn deck. adding more shadowborns increases the score
for comparison, 30 is a very good score
if all my cleric were 3 cmc, then edgewalker would only be saving 33% of the mana cost instead of 100%
with 30 3-cmc clerics
tldr: the quality of cost reduction depends not only on the number of applicable targets, but also the mana curve of those targets

General question: Does anyone else find it annoying when mana rocks or lands are in the "new cards" portion of EDHREC pages? They seem like filler and my brain kinda just shuts off when I see them. They seem unnecessary and almost like they should get thrown down to the Artifacts section if that is possible. Every new commander from C19 I've looked at have had Arcane Signet + 2 Talismans as the first three cards.

I don't know if this is a stupid complaint, but I feel like it detrimentally impacts the commander pages.

Alright, apparently it's only an issue on the Elsha and Pramikon pages :man-shrugging: Arcane SIgnet keeps showing up in the first row on multiple pages though, and I feel like that's a wasted slot like Sol Ring would be.
I overlook mana rocks lots of times. I could use a reminder if there’s an upgrade in the “veggie” department.

I agree that it's a bit annoying. Seeing the lands in the New Cards section seems almost pointless to me as I'm not usually using the site to fill in my mana base. However, it could still be useful to others, so I don't mind much.
Otherwise I’d still be playing keyrunes.
